Therefore, the present invention relates to the following.
[1] An orally administered adsorbent containing surface-modified spherical activated carbon having bulk density from 0.30 g/mL to 0.46 g/mL, a specific surface area determined by the Brunauer-Emmett-Teller (BET) method of not less than 1900 m2/g, total acidic group content from 0.30 meq/g to 1.20 meq/g, and total basic group content from 0.20 meq/g to 0.9 meq/g;
[2] The orally administered adsorbent according to [1], wherein a pore volume of pore diameter from 20 nm to 10,000 nm of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is not greater than 0.21 mL/g;
[3] The orally administered adsorbent according to [1] or [2], wherein a micropore volume ratio (Vm) of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon that is determined by Formula (1) Vm = (V2.0-V1.1)/V(1.1-V0.64) (1) [wherein, in the formula, V2.0, V1.1, and V0.64 are cumulative pore volumes of pore diameter not greater than 2.0 nm, not greater than 1.1 nm, and not greater than 0.64 nm, respectively, calculated by the SF method from nitrogen adsorbed quantity] is not less than 1.0;
[4] The orally administered adsorbent according to any one of [1] to [3], wherein an average particle size of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is from 50 µm to 200 µm;
[5] The orally administered adsorbent according to any one of [1] to [4], wherein the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is prepared using a crosslinked vinyl resin as a carbon source;
[6] A therapeutic or prophylactic agent for a renal disease containing as an active ingredient the orally administered adsorbent described in any one of [1] to [5]; or
[7] A therapeutic or prophylactic agent for a hepatic disease containing as an active ingredient the orally administered adsorbent described in any one of [1] to [5]. Furthermore, the present specification discloses the following.
[8] A method of prophylaxis or therapy of a renal disease or a hepatic disease wherein the orally administered adsorbent described in any one of [1] to [5] is administered in an effective dose to a renal disease or hepatic disease therapy subject;
[9] Surface-modified spherical activated carbon for use in (a) therapy (method) of a renal disease or a hepatic disease,
the surface-modified spherical activated carbon having bulk density from 0.30 g/mL to 0.46 g/mL, a specific surface area determined by the BET method of not less than 1900 m2/g, total acidic group content from 0.30 meq/g to 1.20 meq/g, and total basic group content from 0.20 meq/g to 0.9 meq/g;
[10] The surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to [9], wherein a pore volume of pore diameter from 20 nm to 10,000 nm of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is not greater than 0.21 mL/g;
[11] The surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to [9] or [10], wherein a micropore volume ratio (Vm) of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon that is determined by Formula (1): Vm=V2.0-V1.1/V1.1-V0.64
[wherein, in the formula, V2.0, V1.1, and V0.64 are cumulative pore volumes of pore diameter not greater than 2.0 nm, not greater than 1.1 nm, and not greater than 0.64 nm, respectively, calculated by the Saito-Foley (SF) method from nitrogen adsorbed quantity] is not less than 1.0;
[12] The surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to any one of [9] to [11], wherein an average particle size of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is from 50 µm to 200 µm;
[13] The surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to any one of [9] to [12], wherein the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is prepared using a crosslinked vinyl resin as a carbon source;
[14] Use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon for production of a prophylactic or therapeutic medicine for a renal disease or a hepatic disease,
the surface-modified spherical activated carbon having bulk density from 0.30 g/mL to 0.46 g/mL, a specific surface area determined by the BET method of not less than 1900 m2/g, total acidic group content from 0.30 meq/g to 1.20 meq/g, and total basic group content from 0.20 meq/g to 0.9 meq/g;
[15] The use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to [14], wherein a pore volume of pore diameter from 20 nm to 10,000 nm of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is not greater than 0.21 mL/g;
[16] The use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to [14] or [15], wherein a micropore volume ratio (Vm) of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon that is determined by Formula (1): Vm=V2.0-V1.1/V1.1-V0.64 [wherein, in the formula, V2.0, V1.1, and V0.64 are cumulative pore volumes of pore diameter not greater than 2.0 nm, not greater than 1.1 nm, and not greater than 0.64 nm, respectively, calculated by the SF method from nitrogen adsorbed quantity] is not less than 1;
[17] The use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to any one of [14] to [16], wherein an average particle size of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is from 50 µm to 200 µm;
[18] The use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to any one of [14] to [17], wherein the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is prepared using a crosslinked vinyl resin as a carbon source;
[19] Use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon for prophylaxis or therapy of a renal disease or a hepatic disease,
the surface-modified spherical activated carbon having bulk density from 0.30 g/mL to 0.46 g/mL, a specific surface area determined by the BET method of not less than 1900 m2/g, total acidic group content from 0.30 meq/g to 1.20 meq/g, and total basic group content from 0.20 meq/g to 0.9 meq/g;
[20] The use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to [19], wherein a pore volume of pore diameter from 20 nm to 10,000 nm of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is not greater than 0.21 mL/g;
[21] The use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to [19] or [20], wherein a micropore volume ratio (Vm) of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon that is determined by Formula (1): Vm=V2.0-V1.1/V1.1-V0.64
[wherein, in the formula, V2.0, V1.1, and V0.64 are cumulative pore volumes of pore diameter not greater than 2.0 nm, not greater than 1.1 nm, and not greater than 0.64 nm, respectively, calculated by the SF method from nitrogen adsorbed quantity] is not less than 1.0;
[22] The use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to any one of [19] to [21], wherein an average particle size of the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is from 50 µm to 200 µm;
[23] The use of surface-modified spherical activated carbon according to any one of [19] to [22], wherein the surface-modified spherical activated carbon is prepared using a crosslinked vinyl resin as a carbon source.
